@XTwistedsoulX: actually, it works. The rule about determinating what a spell costs is that you first add at its mana cost every addictional cost, then you apply every cost reduction. So if I want to play a [Capsize](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Capsize) with buyback and with 4 medallions in play, the calculation goes: ![1](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=1&type=symbol)![Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=U&type=symbol)![Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=U&type=symbol) + ![3](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=3&type=symbol) (buyback) - ![4](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=4&type=symbol) (medallions) = ![Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=U&type=symbol)![Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=U&type=symbol).  

Those medallions are a lot of aceleration, in that if you cast 2 spell of the appropriate color is like that they add ![2](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=2&type=symbol) to your mana pool for each medallion. They need a reprint! I've already bought the playset of the blu one, now I'm looking for the red one...!  

5/5

